Sentencas: The concentration, activation, and total polarizations of the cathode in a cathode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) were theoretically and experimentally investigated.
Titulo: Cathode Polarizations of a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: In the theoretical analysis, the exchange current density of the charge transfer was considered to be dependent on the P-O2 determined by the preceding O-2 diffusion, resulting in an interrelationship between activation and concentration polarizations.
Titulo: Cathode Polarizations of a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The established nonlinear polarization equations were then applied to solve the key parameters with area specific resistances and overpotentials of the polarizations experimentally measured by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy on an operating cathode-supported SOFC.
Titulo: Cathode Polarizations of a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: To ensure the consistency and meaningfulness of the solutions, the limiting current density in the concentration polarization equation was first solved, followed by the exchange current density of the activation polarization equation using the predetermined limiting current density.
Titulo: Cathode Polarizations of a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The model was finally verified by comparing the directly measured total overpotentials with the calculated ones using the obtained parameters.
Titulo: Cathode Polarizations of a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The agreement between the two favorably supported the proposed cathode polarization model.
Titulo: Cathode Polarizations of a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
